<Page
    x:Class="ElevateEvansvilleUI.Pages.PlatformPage"
    xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation"
    xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml"
    xmlns:local="using:ElevateEvansvilleUI.Pages"
    xmlns:d="http://schemas.microsoft.com/expression/blend/2008"
    xmlns:mc="http://schemas.openxmlformats.org/markup-compatibility/2006"
    xmlns:controls="using:Microsoft.Toolkit.Uwp.UI.Controls"
    xmlns:toolkit="using:Uno.UI.Toolkit"
    mc:Ignorable="d"  
    d:DesignWidth="1000"
    d:DesignHeight="3000"   
    Background="{ThemeResource ApplicationPageBackgroundThemeBrush}">

    <Page.Resources>
        <Style TargetType="TextBlock">
            <Setter Property="HorizontalAlignment" Value="Left"/>
            <Setter Property="TextWrapping" Value="Wrap"/>
            <Setter Property="FontSize" Value="16"/>
        </Style>

        <Style TargetType="StackPanel">
            <Setter Property="Spacing" Value="10"/>
        </Style>

        <Style TargetType="controls:Expander">
            <Setter Property="IsExpanded" Value="True"/>
            <Setter Property="HorizontalAlignment" Value="Stretch"/>
        </Style>
    </Page.Resources>

    <ScrollViewer>
        <Grid Padding="20,75,20,75" RowSpacing="20" HorizontalAlignment="Center" MaxWidth="900">
            <Grid.RowDefinitions>
                <RowDefinition Height="auto"/>
                <RowDefinition Height="auto"/>
                <RowDefinition Height="auto"/>
                <RowDefinition Height="auto"/>
                <RowDefinition Height="auto"/>
                <RowDefinition Height="auto"/>
                <RowDefinition Height="auto"/>
                <RowDefinition Height="auto"/>
                <RowDefinition Height="auto"/>
                <RowDefinition Height="auto"/>
            </Grid.RowDefinitions>


            <controls:Expander Grid.Row="0">
                <controls:Expander.Header>
                    <Grid>
                        <TextBlock Text="Mission Statement" FontWeight="Bold"/>
                    </Grid>
                </controls:Expander.Header>
                <controls:Expander.Content>
                    <StackPanel>
                        <TextBlock>
                            For 10 years I've lived all over the world, from Asia to Europe, and I'm ready to 
                            bring home what I've learned.
                        </TextBlock>
                        <TextBlock>
                            With a background in military logistics, software engineering, and an aptitude for 
                            disruptive innovation, there is no one better suited to making Evansville one of the 
                            healthiest cities in America.
                        </TextBlock>
                        <TextBlock>
                            In a world strife with uncertainty about the future, I want you to find inspiration to thrive.
                        </TextBlock>
                        
                    </StackPanel>
                </controls:Expander.Content>
            </controls:Expander>

            <controls:Expander Grid.Row="1">
                <controls:Expander.Header>
                    <Grid>
                        <TextBlock Text="City Council" FontWeight="Bold"/>
                        <TextBlock  HorizontalAlignment="Right" FontWeight="Bold">
                            <Hyperlink x:Name="CityCouncilSuggestion" 
                                       NavigateUri="mailto:Tyler.wandtke@ElevateEvansville.com?Subject=City%20Council%20Suggestion">
                                Make a suggestion
                            </Hyperlink>
                        </TextBlock>
                    </Grid>
                </controls:Expander.Header>
                <controls:Expander.Content>
                    <StackPanel>
                        <TextBlock>
                            All powers of the mayor will be dedicated to improving the quality of life and reducing 
                            the cost of living for the working class of Evansville IN. If the decisions of the city 
                            council do not align with that premise, the powers of the mayor will be used to stall or 
                            hinder the degradation of the city.
                        </TextBlock>
                    </StackPanel>
                </controls:Expander.Content>
            </controls:Expander>


            <controls:Expander Grid.Row="2">
                <controls:Expander.Header>
                    <Grid>
                        <TextBlock Text="Corruption" FontWeight="Bold"/>
                        <TextBlock  HorizontalAlignment="Right" FontWeight="Bold">
                            <Hyperlink x:Name="CorruptionSuggestion" 
                                       NavigateUri="mailto:Tyler.wandtke@ElevateEvansville.com?Subject=Corruption%20Suggestion">
                                Make a suggestion
                            </Hyperlink>
                        </TextBlock>
                    </Grid>
                </controls:Expander.Header>
                <controls:Expander.Content>
                    <StackPanel>
                        <TextBlock>
                            Publicly elected members of the city will only accept income of considerable size from their offices salary.
                        </TextBlock>
                        <TextBlock>
                            Embezzlement of city funds <Bold>will not</Bold> be tolerated at any level.
                        </TextBlock>
                        <TextBlock>
                            A publicly elected member of the city will not use their position of authority to enrich themselves, their close
                            associates, their friends, or their family.
                        </TextBlock>
                        <TextBlock>
                            Publicly elected officials will be required to forfeit their stock holdings prior to holding office. Owned assets
                            that will passively generate income must be placed in a blind trust or handed off to a trusted associate.
                        </TextBlock>
                        <TextBlock>
                            <Bold>All</Bold> publicly elected officials will be denied access to their office's authority until proof the prior
                            requirements are met.
                        </TextBlock>
                    </StackPanel>
                </controls:Expander.Content>
            </controls:Expander>

            <controls:Expander Grid.Row="1" Visibility="Collapsed">
                <controls:Expander.Header>
                    <Grid>
                        <TextBlock Text="Business Relations and Permits" FontWeight="Bold"/>
                        <TextBlock  HorizontalAlignment="Right" FontWeight="Bold" >
                            <Hyperlink x:Name="PermitsSuggestion"
                                       NavigateUri="mailto:Tyler.wandtke@ElevateEvansville.com?Subject=Business%20Relations%20and%20Permits%20Suggestion">
                                Make a suggestion
                            </Hyperlink>
                        </TextBlock>
                    </Grid>
                </controls:Expander.Header>
                <controls:Expander.Content>
                    <StackPanel>
                        <TextBlock>
                            The city of Evansville will be prioritizing companies, businesses, enterprises, ventures, and
                            organizations that will have a direct or indirect impact on human longevity. They must value the 
                            objective good above any obligation they may have to shareholders or partners.
                        </TextBlock>

                        <TextBlock>
                            Business endeavors in the following fields will be highly regarded by the office of the mayor:
                        </TextBlock>

                        <TextBlock>
                            <Hyperlink NavigateUri="https://www.health.harvard.edu/topics/exercise-and-fitness#:~:text=Exercising%20regularly%2C%20every%20day%20if%20possible%2C%20is%20the,disease%2C%20stroke%2C%20diabetes%2C%20dementia%2C%20depression%2C%20and%20many%20cancers.">
                                Health and Fitness
                            </Hyperlink>
                        </TextBlock>

                        <TextBlock>
                            <Hyperlink NavigateUri="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Vertical_farming">
                                Vertical Farming
                            </Hyperlink>
                        </TextBlock>

                        <TextBlock>
                            Broadband / Fibre Optic Internet Expansion
                        </TextBlock>

                        <TextBlock>
                            Grocery Delivery Services
                        </TextBlock>

                        <TextBlock>
                            Innovative Transportation Solutions
                        </TextBlock>

                        <TextBlock>
                            Research and Development Institutions 
                        </TextBlock>

                        <TextBlock>
                            Education and Medical Facilities
                        </TextBlock>

                        <TextBlock>
                            Solar and Nuclear Energy Solutions
                        </TextBlock>


                    </StackPanel>
                </controls:Expander.Content>
            </controls:Expander>
            
            
            <controls:Expander  Grid.Row="3">
                <controls:Expander.Header>
                    <Grid>
                        <TextBlock Text="Police" FontWeight="Bold"/>
                        <TextBlock HorizontalAlignment="Right" FontWeight="Bold">
                            <Hyperlink x:Name="PoliceSuggestion"
                                       NavigateUri="mailto:Tyler.wandtke@ElevateEvansville.com?Subject=Police%20Suggestion">
                                Make a suggestion
                            </Hyperlink>
                        </TextBlock>
                    </Grid>
                </controls:Expander.Header>
                <controls:Expander.Content>
                    <StackPanel>
                        <TextBlock>
                            The Evansville Vanderburgh Police Department will at no point be utilized as an occupying 
                            force to harass, intimidate, coerce or discourage the working class of Evansville, IN.
                        </TextBlock>

                        <TextBlock>
                            The police will not be utilized as a personal militia for the advancement of private capital.
                        </TextBlock>

                        <TextBlock>
                            The police will recognize all protests that value equality, justice, and the objective good. 
                            Actors that wish to subvert, minimize, or halt these causes through violent means will not be 
                            tolerated.
                        </TextBlock>

                        <TextBlock>
                            Rehabilitation will be the primary focus of future crime prevention.
                        </TextBlock>
                       
                        <TextBlock>
                            Recreational drugs will not be criminalized unless in extreme circumstances such as large-scale illegal smuggling.
                        </TextBlock>

                        <TextBlock>
                            On duty officers that are stationed at public schools will <Bold><Underline>not</Underline></Bold> wear their uniforms in an effort
                            to improve student mental health.
                        </TextBlock>

                        <TextBlock>
                            Teenagers and children who have been unlawfully arrested for non-violent, perceived, behavioral issues by 
                            school-stationed police will have their records cleared. Repeating juveniles will also be given every opportunity
                            for rehabilitation by the appropriate servicing agents.
                        </TextBlock>

                        <TextBlock>
                            The Evansville Police Department will <Bold>NOT</Bold> be defunded. The city budget will be allocated accordingly to 
                            ensure maximum efficiency and professionalism of policing, mental health services, and domestic abuse responders.
                        </TextBlock>

                        <TextBlock>
                            A police registrar will be available for citizens to rate the performance and behavior of each individual officer. 
                            If the officer has been flagged enough for behavioral issues that officer will be released or placed on desk duties 
                            depending on the severity of their actions.
                        </TextBlock>
                        
                        
                    </StackPanel>

                </controls:Expander.Content>
            </controls:Expander>

            <controls:Expander Grid.Row="4">
                <controls:Expander.Header>
                    <Grid>
                        <TextBlock Text="Crime Reduction" FontWeight="Bold"/>
                        <TextBlock HorizontalAlignment="Right" FontWeight="Bold">
                            <Hyperlink x:Name="CrimeReductionSuggestion"
                                       NavigateUri="mailto:Tyler.wandtke@ElevateEvansville.com?Subject=Crime%20Reduction%20Suggestion">
                                Make a suggestion
                            </Hyperlink>
                        </TextBlock>
                    </Grid>
                </controls:Expander.Header>
                <controls:Expander.Content>
                    <StackPanel>
                        <TextBlock>
                            There is one common denominator among all petty crimes in every city around the world, <Underline>Poverty.</Underline>
                        </TextBlock>
                        
                        <TextBlock>
                            The core platform of this campaign is to reduce the cost of living and increase the quality of life.
                            If successful, the crime rate of Evansville will naturally decrease as its citizens begin to 
                            thrive economically.
                        </TextBlock>
                        
                        <TextBlock>
                            Once the economic situation of the working class of Evansville has improved, the core focus of crime reduction
                            will be shifted to <Hyperlink NavigateUri="https://www.fbi.gov/investigate/white-collar-crime">white-collar crimes.</Hyperlink>
                        </TextBlock>

                        <TextBlock>
                            Fines for crimes such as illegal parking or speeding through an intersection will scale with the individuals income rather
                            than being a fixed rate, crimes committed by juveniles will be fined based on their parents income.
                        </TextBlock>

                        <TextBlock>
                            Misdemeanor courts will no longer engage in the practice of 
                            <Hyperlink NavigateUri="https://www.brennancenter.org/our-work/research-reports/how-cash-bail-works#:~:text=Cash%20bail%20is%20used%20as%20a%20guarantee%20that,have%20broad%20discretion%20to%20raise%20or%20lower%20it.">
                                cash bails.
                            </Hyperlink>
                            
                            Cash bails for more agregious crimes will scale with an individuals income.
                        </TextBlock>
                    </StackPanel>
                </controls:Expander.Content>
            </controls:Expander>

            <controls:Expander  Grid.Row="5">
                <controls:Expander.Header>
                    <Grid>
                        <TextBlock Text="School Board" FontWeight="Bold"/>
                        <TextBlock HorizontalAlignment="Right" FontWeight="Bold">
                            <Hyperlink x:Name="SchoolBoardSuggestion"
                                       NavigateUri="mailto:Tyler.wandtke@ElevateEvansville.com?Subject=School%20Board%20Suggestion">
                                Make a suggestion
                            </Hyperlink>
                        </TextBlock>
                    </Grid>
                </controls:Expander.Header>
                <controls:Expander.Content>
                    <StackPanel>
                        <TextBlock>
                            The Evansville Vanderburgh School Corporation will in no way discriminate, minimize, 
                            ignore, or deny the existence of minority groups of people or atrocities of history 
                            despite any efforts to limit exposure by State or Federal officials.
                        </TextBlock>

                        <TextBlock>
                            Teachers will be paid proportionally in accordance with inflation to allow a comfortable and decent 
                            standard of living.
                        </TextBlock>

                        <TextBlock>
                            All students Grades 1-12 will be provided free, nutritious, high quality meals for breakfast and lunch.
                        </TextBlock>

                        <TextBlock>
                            School hours will be adjusted to match the average of the local working class hours. (9 a.m. – 3.p.m)
                        </TextBlock>
                        
                    </StackPanel>

                </controls:Expander.Content>
            </controls:Expander>

            <controls:Expander  Grid.Row="6">
                <controls:Expander.Header>
                    <Grid>
                        <TextBlock Text="Housing" FontWeight="Bold"/>
                        <TextBlock HorizontalAlignment="Right" FontWeight="Bold">
                            <Hyperlink x:Name="HousingSuggestion"
                                       NavigateUri="mailto:Tyler.wandtke@ElevateEvansville.com?Subject=Housing%20Suggestion">
                                Make a suggestion
                            </Hyperlink>
                        </TextBlock>
                    </Grid>
                </controls:Expander.Header>
                <controls:Expander.Content>
                    <StackPanel>
                        <TextBlock>
                            The city of Evansville will be modifying the existing affordable housing program and the 
                            Evansville Housing Authority into a newly formed Housing Department.
                        </TextBlock>

                        <TextBlock>
                            The Evansville Public Housing Department (EVPHD) will invest in and renovate old buildings 
                            and failing apartment complexes randomly across the city, these new investments will be marked 
                            40-50% cheaper than their private counterparts. The quality of these dwellings will also vary 
                            depending on location and probable tenets will not be aware of what is city managed and what it 
                            is privately managed.
                        </TextBlock>

                        <TextBlock>
                            The housing provided by the EVPHD will become a direct source of revenue for city, once enacted it 
                            will give the city the opportunity to reach an equilibrium and lower property taxes across the board, 
                            thus decreasing the cost of living for all.
                        </TextBlock>

                    </StackPanel>

                </controls:Expander.Content>
            </controls:Expander>

            <controls:Expander  Grid.Row="7">
                <controls:Expander.Header>
                    <Grid>
                        <TextBlock Text="Transportation" FontWeight="Bold"/>
                        <TextBlock HorizontalAlignment="Right" FontWeight="Bold">
                            <Hyperlink x:Name="TransportationSuggestion"
                                       NavigateUri="mailto:Tyler.wandtke@ElevateEvansville.com?Subject=Transportation%20Suggestion">
                                Make a suggestion
                            </Hyperlink>
                        </TextBlock>
                    </Grid>
                </controls:Expander.Header>
                <controls:Expander.Content>
                    <StackPanel>
                        <TextBlock>
                            The city of Evansville will undergo a large-scale endeavor to reduce its dependence on vehicles and 
                            fossil fuels through the utilization of <Hyperlink NavigateUri="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Light_rail"> light rail infrastructure. </Hyperlink> 
                            Where applicable, existing roads will be converted into light rail tracks.
                        </TextBlock>

                        <TextBlock>
                            To offset traffic congestion any and all intersections that are capable will be converted into 
                            <Hyperlink NavigateUri="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Roundabout#:~:text=A%20roundabout%20is%20a%20type%20of%20circular%20intersection,typically%20given%20to%20traffic%20already%20in%20the%20junction.">
                                roundabouts.
                            </Hyperlink>
                        </TextBlock>

                        <TextBlock>
                            Residents of Evansville will ideally never be more than a 20-30 minute walk from a light rail station.
                        </TextBlock>

                        <TextBlock>
                            The Metropolitan Evansville Transit System will be converted to primarily run light rail scheduling with 
                            supplemental busses wherever the need arises.
                        </TextBlock>
                    </StackPanel>

                </controls:Expander.Content>
            </controls:Expander>

            <controls:Expander  Grid.Row="8">
                <controls:Expander.Header>
                    <Grid>
                        <TextBlock Text="Parks and Recreations" FontWeight="Bold"/>
                        <TextBlock HorizontalAlignment="Right" FontWeight="Bold">
                            <Hyperlink x:Name="RecreationsSuggestion"
                                       NavigateUri="mailto:Tyler.wandtke@ElevateEvansville.com?Subject=Parks%20and%20Recreations%20Suggestion">
                                Make a suggestion
                            </Hyperlink>
                        </TextBlock>
                    </Grid>
                </controls:Expander.Header>
                <controls:Expander.Content>
                    <StackPanel>
                        <TextBlock>
                            As the city moves forward with its transportation overhaul, the parks and recreation department will 
                            spearhead the forestation and walkability of the city. Fully-grown adult trees will be relocated 
                            within city limits and will be strategically placed to cover exposed asphalt, blacktop, and concrete. 
                            New trees will be planted from wherever the old ones were located.
                        </TextBlock>
                    </StackPanel>

                </controls:Expander.Content>
            </controls:Expander>


            <controls:Expander Grid.Row="9">
                <controls:Expander.Header>
                    <Grid>
                        <TextBlock Text="Final Remarks" FontWeight="Bold"/>
                        <TextBlock HorizontalAlignment="Right" FontWeight="Bold">
                            <Hyperlink x:Name="FinalSuggestion"
                                       NavigateUri="mailto:Tyler.wandtke@ElevateEvansville.com?Subject=Parks%20and%20Recreations%20Suggestion">
                                Make a suggestion
                            </Hyperlink>
                        </TextBlock>
                    </Grid>
                </controls:Expander.Header>
                <controls:Expander.Content>
                    <StackPanel>
                        <TextBlock>
                            Each item in this platform will be viewed as a task to complete, each one will be accomplished as quickly as the powers 
                            of the mayor will allow. Some items may need to be accomplished before others to maximize effectiveness.
                        </TextBlock>

                        <TextBlock>
                            Delaying the completion of these tasks for election convenience will not be considered.
                        </TextBlock>

                        <TextBlock>
                            Opponents to accomplishing these tasks will become highlighted as obstacles to Evansvilles propserity and will need to prepare
                            their defense to their constituents next election cycle.
                        </TextBlock>
                       
                        
                    </StackPanel>

                </controls:Expander.Content>
            </controls:Expander>

        </Grid>
    </ScrollViewer>

</Page>
